# POS System Implementation Rules

## Core POS Features
- Real-time order processing with instant updates
- Quick menu item selection with touch-friendly interface
- Table management and reservation system
- Multiple payment method support (cash, card, digital)
- Receipt generation and printing functionality

## Order Management
- Real-time order status updates across all interfaces
- Order modification capabilities (add/remove items)
- Order splitting for shared tables
- Order history and transaction tracking
- Integration with kitchen display systems

## Payment Processing
- Cash transaction handling with change calculation
- Credit card processing integration
- Digital payment methods support
- Receipt generation with customizable formats
- Payment reconciliation and reporting

## User Interface Requirements
- Touch-optimized interface for tablet/mobile use
- Keyboard shortcuts for power users
- Quick action buttons for common operations
- Responsive design for various screen sizes
- Accessibility compliance for all users

## Integration Points
- Real-time inventory synchronization
- Kitchen display system integration
- Customer profile and loyalty program connection
- Analytics and reporting dashboard integration
- Notification system for order updates

## Performance & Reliability
- Offline mode capability for network outages
- Data synchronization when connection restored
- Fast response times for high-volume periods
- Error handling and recovery mechanisms
- Backup and data protection features

